Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 20:20:23 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] Rename Engineering Manager, add Planner nav link, add
 per-department admin links (item 1)

- "Engineering Manager" -> "Engineering Dashboard" in the sidebar
- Added "Planner" nav link (gated on the new unit:plan permission)
- Mission Control confirmed/kept first in the nav order
- Admins (config:manage) now see a "Departments" section in the sidebar
  listing every active department in sortOrder, each linking to Mission
  Control pre-filtered to that department
  (/mission-control?departmentId=...) - not a separate page per
  department, which would duplicate a lot of UI; Mission Control
  already supports department filtering server-side, this just makes
  it reachable with one click per department instead of using the
  dropdown every time
- Mission Control now reads departmentId from the URL on load and uses
  it as the filter, taking priority over the existing "auto-default to
  a scoped user's own department" logic. Required wrapping the page in
  a Suspense boundary since useSearchParams() needs one in the Next.js
  App Router.
