From 6e5b5e7a743ce1acb138293dd5695549b92b7746 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 20:20:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] Add direct Task Completed button on Mission Control cards
 (item 5)

Removed the requirement to open the side drawer, click Start, then
reopen and click Complete. Every card for a Ready or InProgress task
now has a "Task Completed" button directly on it - one click completes
the task and lets the existing routing-advance logic move it to the
next station automatically, exactly like before, just without the
detour through the drawer for the common case.

The drawer isn't gone - clicking anywhere else on the card still opens
it (needed for notes, history, and verification), and if a task turns
out to require a checklist that isn't complete yet, the direct-complete
click fails with 422 and automatically opens the drawer instead so the
checklist can actually be filled in there - the one case that genuinely
needs more UI than a single button can offer.
---
